Kisorio broke away in the final 10 kilometres to win in a time of 2 hours, 7 minutes and 6 seconds, shaving 10 seconds off the course record set six years ago by Tadese Tola of Ethopia. His compatriots Solomon Kirwa Yego and Emmanuel Rutto finished second and third respectively. In the women's race, Sutume Asefa Kebede of Ethopia secured her maiden marathon title, clocking 2 hours, 23 minutes and 31 seconds. Li Zhixuan was second with Mulu Seboka Seyfu of Ethiopia finished third. --Reuters-- 